This is a sample English learning document for intermediate students. 

It contains grammar rules about present perfect tense, vocabulary words related to travel and daily routines, and reading comprehension exercises. 

The document is designed for B1 level learners who want to improve their English skills. It includes various topics such as describing past experiences, talking about hobbies, and understanding travel vocabulary. 

Practice exercises help students develop listening, speaking, reading, and writing skills. The grammar section explains how to use "have/has + past participle" to talk about completed actions. 

Vocabulary section includes words like: journey, destination, accommodation, itinerary, sightseeing, and adventure. 

Reading comprehension passage is about a student's summer vacation in Europe, with questions testing understanding of main ideas and details.